WEBVTT

1
00:02:28.148 --> 00:02:29.148
What?

2
00:02:34.029 --> 00:02:35.864
I can't understand.

3
00:02:46.833 --> 00:02:48.460
Speak plainly.

4
00:02:54.049 --> 00:02:55.050
{\an8}Stop.

5
00:02:55.884 --> 00:02:57.177
{\an8}Stop it.

6
00:03:29.292 --> 00:03:32.045
There's been a raven.

7
00:03:35.674 --> 00:03:37.676
Good morrow. Your Grace.

8
00:03:38.510 --> 00:03:41.346
Slept well.
I trust?

9
00:03:41.721 --> 00:03:44.224
As I said.
there's been a raven.

10
00:03:46.601 --> 00:03:49.979
Aegon's army departed King's Landing
a fortnight ago.

11
00:03:49.980 --> 00:03:52.419
The castles of Rosby
and Stokeworth

12
00:03:52.420 --> 00:03:54.807
have both fallen
without siege.

13
00:03:54.808 --> 00:03:57.194
They have raised
Aegon's banner

14
00:03:57.195 --> 00:04:00.699
and added their levies
to Ser Criston Cole's host.

15
00:04:01.616 --> 00:04:04.326
Both houses cited that

16
00:04:04.327 --> 00:04:07.914
sad business with the usurper's son
in their declarations.

17
00:04:09.040 --> 00:04:10.583
Ser Criston's army.

18
00:04:11.292 --> 00:04:13.752
now tripled in strength.

19
00:04:13.753 --> 00:04:16.672
might have Harrenhal
as its destination.

20
00:04:16.673 --> 00:04:20.051
Even if you can raise a host of Rivermen.

21
00:04:20.052 --> 00:04:23.054
they will not be ready
in time to face him.

22
00:04:29.227 --> 00:04:32.063
Let's see what your Lord Paramount
is made of.

23
00:04:37.736 --> 00:04:41.031
My prince...
Uh. My-My Grace.

24
00:04:41.032 --> 00:04:42.490
Your Grace.

25
00:04:43.408 --> 00:04:46.453
Lord Grover is looking more hale
and healthy than I expected.

26
00:04:46.454 --> 00:04:47.850
Uh. this is
Ser Oscar Tully.

27
00:04:47.851 --> 00:04:49.382
grandson
to Grover Tully.

28
00:04:49.383 --> 00:04:50.914
He is heir
to Riverrun

29
00:04:50.915 --> 00:04:54.251
and the future
Lord Paramount of the Riverlands.

30
00:04:54.252 --> 00:04:57.588
His Grace. the King Consort.
Daemon Targaryen.

31
00:04:57.589 --> 00:05:00.884
- It is an honor. Your Grace.
- Indeed.

32
00:05:06.765 --> 00:05:08.808
How fares
your grandsire?

33
00:05:12.771 --> 00:05:15.773
Sadly. he remains
incapacitated.

34
00:05:15.774 --> 00:05:18.776
He lies in a kind of
waking sleep.

35
00:05:18.777 --> 00:05:22.322
unable to do much more
than take meager drink.

36
00:05:22.323 --> 00:05:24.949
It is barely enough
to sustain him.

37
00:05:24.950 --> 00:05:27.055
So. he's alive?

38
00:05:27.056 --> 00:05:29.161
Yes. gods be good.

39
00:05:29.162 --> 00:05:31.705
Well. my time is short
and I have need of an army.

40
00:05:31.706 --> 00:05:34.250
Perhaps you might
place a feather pillow over his head

41
00:05:34.251 --> 00:05:36.503
and speed along
your inheritance?

42
00:05:38.630 --> 00:05:42.300
I-I love my grandsire.
like a father.

43
00:05:42.967 --> 00:05:46.638
My own lord father died suddenly.
himself a young man.

44
00:05:47.305 --> 00:05:49.933
Lord Grover raised me
in his stead.

45
00:05:49.934 --> 00:05:51.308
All very touching.

46
00:05:51.309 --> 00:05:53.311
Are you here to speak
with your grandsire's voice?

47
00:05:53.312 --> 00:05:55.313
For House Tully
and the Riverlands?

48
00:05:55.314 --> 00:05:56.815
While he still lives?

49
00:05:59.484 --> 00:06:03.238
- That is not our way.
- Then you're of no use to me.

50
00:06:03.905 --> 00:06:05.699
I can see why the Blackwoods
and the Brackens

51
00:06:05.700 --> 00:06:07.032
did not fear
to start a war

52
00:06:07.033 --> 00:06:09.368
beneath the nose
of their liege lords.

53
00:06:09.369 --> 00:06:11.704
House Tully is
a fish with no head.

54
00:06:11.705 --> 00:06:13.706
Remind me which
of your countrymen

55
00:06:13.707 --> 00:06:15.833
claim to fight
in the name of Aegon?

56
00:06:15.834 --> 00:06:17.960
Was it. was it
Bracken or Blackwood?

57
00:06:17.961 --> 00:06:20.672
It was House Bracken
that declared Green. Your Grace.

58
00:06:20.673 --> 00:06:21.881
Who could remember.

59
00:06:23.049 --> 00:06:24.112
Summon
the Blackwoods here.

60
00:06:24.113 --> 00:06:25.175
I require
men of action

61
00:06:25.176 --> 00:06:27.178
to lead my host
of Rivermen.

62
00:06:56.041 --> 00:06:57.459
M'lady.

63
00:07:01.046 --> 00:07:04.716
"Princess." if we're
holding to formalities.

64
00:07:04.717 --> 00:07:07.385
Apologies.
Princess.

65
00:07:08.762 --> 00:07:11.097
And you are Alyn.

66
00:07:11.098 --> 00:07:13.433
Yes. Princess.

67
00:07:14.809 --> 00:07:16.436
I'm given to understand
my lord husband

68
00:07:16.437 --> 00:07:18.313
owes you his life.

69
00:07:21.483 --> 00:07:24.611
But I was not told
his savior was so comely.

70
00:07:25.820 --> 00:07:28.405
Your mother must've
been very beautiful.

71
00:07:28.406 --> 00:07:30.742
Rhaenys.

72
00:07:38.166 --> 00:07:40.794
- Is your work finished?
- No. m'lord.

73
00:07:51.763 --> 00:07:53.765
I just had a word
with your captains.

74
00:07:55.809 --> 00:07:59.270
He was the sailor who plucked you
from your watery grave?

75
00:08:06.861 --> 00:08:07.862
Yes.

76
00:08:09.364 --> 00:08:11.032
You did not think
to mention it?

77
00:08:11.991 --> 00:08:13.785
I did not think
it relevant.

78
00:08:16.037 --> 00:08:18.039
I know who he is.
Corlys.

79
00:08:20.458 --> 00:08:24.087
Alyn's past is
no fault of his.

80
00:08:24.088 --> 00:08:25.170
He saved
his lord's life.

81
00:08:25.171 --> 00:08:26.464
He should be raised up
and honored.

82
00:08:26.465 --> 00:08:27.799
not hidden
beneath the tides.

83
00:08:27.800 --> 00:08:29.801
Is this why you came?

84
00:08:30.885 --> 00:08:32.637
To subject me
to an inquisition?

85
00:08:34.806 --> 00:08:38.643
I came to tell you that Baela
has called me to Dragonstone.

86
00:08:38.644 --> 00:08:41.020
Baela?

87
00:08:41.021 --> 00:08:43.690
That council is going to dine on her
and Jace for supper.

88
00:08:43.691 --> 00:08:45.859
They grow restless
in Rhaenyra's absence.

89
00:08:45.860 --> 00:08:49.319
Still...
Where has that woman gone?

90
00:08:49.320 --> 00:08:52.991
I suspect to try and draw us all back
from the abyss.

91
00:09:15.013 --> 00:09:18.224
- Good morrow. Your Grace.
- Good morrow. Grand Maester.

92
00:09:22.020 --> 00:09:23.688
As requested.

93
00:09:24.689 --> 00:09:27.275
- I brewed it myself.
- Thank you.

94
00:09:28.276 --> 00:09:30.362
I will see it
delivered discreetly.

95
00:09:31.780 --> 00:09:36.034
Do report if the recipient
has need of any remedy.

96
00:09:36.035 --> 00:09:39.204
The tea is known
to disagree with the gut.

97
00:09:39.205 --> 00:09:41.414
I shall observe
the girl closely.

98
00:09:47.962 --> 00:09:49.589
Grand Maester.

99
00:09:55.595 --> 00:09:58.055
You've ever been
a practical man.

100
00:09:58.056 --> 00:10:00.517
an honorable servant
to the crown.

101
00:10:01.267 --> 00:10:04.521
And you served my lord husband
in his darkest hours.

102
00:10:04.938 --> 00:10:07.148
Such was my duty.
Your Grace.

103
00:10:08.566 --> 00:10:09.776
Tell me.

104
00:10:12.070 --> 00:10:15.198
Do you believe Viserys wanted
Aegon to succeed him?

105
00:10:19.619 --> 00:10:21.830
I could not know.

106
00:10:23.748 --> 00:10:26.751
His Grace never raised
the matter with me.

107
00:11:26.353 --> 00:11:27.895
Ser Criston Cole's host

108
00:11:27.896 --> 00:11:29.439
has taken to exploiting
the tree cover

109
00:11:29.440 --> 00:11:30.899
to conceal
its movements.

110
00:11:30.900 --> 00:11:32.296
He now only
travels by night

111
00:11:32.297 --> 00:11:33.692
to confound
our dragons.

112
00:11:33.693 --> 00:11:35.444
And what is Cole's heading?

113
00:11:35.445 --> 00:11:37.197
It is difficult to say.
but there were signs

114
00:11:37.198 --> 00:11:39.491
of an army moving
northwest. I believe.

115
00:11:39.492 --> 00:11:41.784
She believes.

116
00:11:41.785 --> 00:11:43.828
You should've burned them
when you had the chance.

117
00:11:43.829 --> 00:11:44.995
Perhaps you can.
Ser Alfred.

118
00:11:44.996 --> 00:11:46.663
when you next sight
them on your dragon.

119
00:11:46.664 --> 00:11:50.001
The only reason we know any of this

120
00:11:50.002 --> 00:11:51.627
is because
of Baela's efforts.

121
00:11:51.628 --> 00:11:53.650
What do we know. my prince?

122
00:11:53.651 --> 00:11:55.673
If you ask me.
it is little and less.

123
00:11:55.674 --> 00:11:58.385
We know that Cole possesses
a host that is growing in strength

124
00:11:58.386 --> 00:11:59.677
and that it
is a problem.

125
00:11:59.678 --> 00:12:01.054
Can Daemon
hope to meet it

126
00:12:01.055 --> 00:12:02.638
with his own
in time?

127
00:12:02.639 --> 00:12:03.847
And if I know
the Riverlands.

128
00:12:03.848 --> 00:12:05.892
he has more
disentangling ahead of him

129
00:12:05.893 --> 00:12:09.144
than the end
of a Lyseni orgy.

130
00:12:09.145 --> 00:12:12.607
Have you heard word
from your father?

131
00:12:15.193 --> 00:12:18.529
- No.
- Ravens were sent to Harrenhal

132
00:12:18.530 --> 00:12:21.866
seeking news of Daemon's progress
with the Riverlords.

133
00:12:21.867 --> 00:12:24.369
None have.
as yet. returned.

134
00:12:24.370 --> 00:12:25.994
Just so.

135
00:12:25.995 --> 00:12:28.414
An enemy host.
growing in constitution.

136
00:12:28.415 --> 00:12:32.710
marches somewhere
in the vastness of the Crownlands.

137
00:12:32.711 --> 00:12:37.007
We could. perhaps.
act if only we had a host of our own.

138
00:12:37.008 --> 00:12:38.425
Or someone here to lead us.

139
00:12:39.050 --> 00:12:40.885
Mind your tongue.
Ser Alfred.

140
00:12:42.387 --> 00:12:44.848
Does it speak falsely.
my prince?

141
00:12:44.849 --> 00:12:47.266
This council
is rudderless.

142
00:12:47.267 --> 00:12:49.561
I'm doing my best
to steer it. Ser Alfred.

143
00:12:51.146 --> 00:12:54.858
Why should your voice
be any louder than ours. Princess?

144
00:12:54.859 --> 00:12:56.734
The queen did not
name you Hand.

145
00:12:56.735 --> 00:12:59.236
It is her voice.
and that of the king consort.

146
00:12:59.237 --> 00:13:02.531
that we need to raise alliances
and command our vassals.

147
00:13:02.532 --> 00:13:05.744
- But they are gone.
- What has come of this council?

148
00:13:10.790 --> 00:13:12.250
My lord.

149
00:13:15.253 --> 00:13:18.630
Our enemy
is on the march.

150
00:13:18.631 --> 00:13:20.759
Is there naught to be done
in the absence of the queen.

151
00:13:20.760 --> 00:13:24.095
but to grouse
and claw for power?

152
00:13:30.185 --> 00:13:32.604
We do not know
the queen's doings.

153
00:13:33.772 --> 00:13:36.274
But we must trust
that she seeks the same

154
00:13:36.275 --> 00:13:38.360
as each of us
at this table.

155
00:13:39.986 --> 00:13:42.447
An end to this conflict.

156
00:14:04.302 --> 00:14:06.804
Men of House Darklyn.

157
00:14:06.805 --> 00:14:11.976
All who bend the knee to the true king.
Aegon. will be spared.

158
00:14:11.977 --> 00:14:14.646
You can earn back
your honor by raising his banner

159
00:14:14.647 --> 00:14:16.480
and fighting
in his name

160
00:14:16.481 --> 00:14:19.150
against the
Whore of Dragonstone.

161
00:14:20.151 --> 00:14:22.153
All who refuse...

162
00:14:23.571 --> 00:14:25.573
will have their death.

163
00:14:39.671 --> 00:14:41.297
Good morrow.
Lord Darklyn.

164
00:14:42.007 --> 00:14:45.510
Is there no honor left
in this world. Cole?

165
00:14:45.511 --> 00:14:47.929
Sacking your
queen's own castles

166
00:14:47.930 --> 00:14:50.348
and putting
her people to the sword?

167
00:14:50.349 --> 00:14:52.017
"Kingmaker."

168
00:14:56.354 --> 00:14:58.732
You are not fit
for the white cloak.

169
00:15:02.193 --> 00:15:05.238
This is a better death
than a traitor deserves.

170
00:15:05.739 --> 00:15:07.949
You should
thank me for it.

171
00:15:10.076 --> 00:15:13.079
Yours will come in kind.

172
00:15:27.635 --> 00:15:28.887
Lord Hand.

173
00:15:44.319 --> 00:15:46.571
We'll lead
the van northeast.

174
00:15:46.572 --> 00:15:48.031
follow the coastline.

175
00:15:49.449 --> 00:15:51.116
I realize you were
neither born nor bred

176
00:15:51.117 --> 00:15:54.537
anywhere near the Crownlands.
my good Lord Hand.

177
00:15:54.538 --> 00:15:56.956
but Harrenhal
is to the west.

178
00:16:01.002 --> 00:16:02.629
Indeed it is.

179
00:16:05.507 --> 00:16:08.760
Fuck you. I told you
we should've sent our dragons.

180
00:16:08.761 --> 00:16:10.595
And now look
what's happened.

181
00:16:11.012 --> 00:16:13.660
Daemon. of all people.
has taken Harrenhal.

182
00:16:13.661 --> 00:16:16.309
I give you a job.
and now you just sit there.

183
00:16:16.310 --> 00:16:18.770
It's your
fucking castle!

184
00:16:20.522 --> 00:16:24.567
Well. that castle is
more crippled than I am. Your Grace.

185
00:16:25.819 --> 00:16:27.278
It's like to drive
Daemon to madness

186
00:16:27.279 --> 00:16:28.738
as he attempts
to make use of it.

187
00:16:28.739 --> 00:16:31.116
It is beyond
his faculties.

188
00:16:31.866 --> 00:16:35.912
It is also penniless.
as I happily control all of its gold.

189
00:16:35.913 --> 00:16:39.498
So. as Harrenhal saps
Daemon's resolve.

190
00:16:39.499 --> 00:16:41.959
the false queen remains
trapped on her island.

191
00:16:41.960 --> 00:16:45.296
and Ser Criston continues felling castles
in the Crownlands.

192
00:16:45.297 --> 00:16:47.382
Wh...

193
00:16:47.799 --> 00:16:49.988
I need to be informed
of these things

194
00:16:49.989 --> 00:16:52.177
if I am to make
informed rulings.

195
00:16:52.178 --> 00:16:54.138
I will not be made
to look a fool in front of

196
00:16:54.139 --> 00:16:56.808
- my allies and enemies.
- Harrenhal must wait.

197
00:17:00.353 --> 00:17:03.523
Ser Criston is marching
on Rook's Rest.

198
00:17:03.524 --> 00:17:05.315
Rook's Re...
A pathetic prize.

199
00:17:05.316 --> 00:17:07.485
- I gave no such command...
- The castle is small.

200
00:17:08.653 --> 00:17:09.987
weakly defended.

201
00:17:09.988 --> 00:17:13.116
and Lord Staunton sits
on Rhaenyra's council.

202
00:17:13.117 --> 00:17:15.325
After Cole smashes it.

203
00:17:15.326 --> 00:17:17.662
we'll have Dragonstone
effectively cut off by land.

204
00:17:19.372 --> 00:17:22.333
This war will not be won
with dragons alone.

205
00:17:22.334 --> 00:17:25.753
but with dragons flying
behind armies of men.

206
00:17:25.754 --> 00:17:29.174
No! Have him turn about.
I want Harrenhal back.

207
00:17:30.342 --> 00:17:32.510
Cole is already
preparing his attack.

208
00:17:34.012 --> 00:17:36.013
Uh. how-how do
you know this?

209
00:17:36.014 --> 00:17:38.016
He sent word to me.

210
00:17:39.017 --> 00:17:40.185
To you?

211
00:17:43.021 --> 00:17:45.315
The two of you
have been

212
00:17:45.732 --> 00:17:49.694
plotting...
without my authority?

213
00:18:10.715 --> 00:18:11.758
Mm.

214
00:18:45.458 --> 00:18:46.459
Mm.

215
00:18:52.424 --> 00:18:54.758
Harrenhal is
a useful morass.

216
00:18:54.759 --> 00:18:57.762
It will keep Daemon well-occupied while
we strengthen our host

217
00:18:57.763 --> 00:19:00.410
and weaken Rhaenyra's
support on the mainland.

218
00:19:00.411 --> 00:19:03.924
We will deal with it
in the Riverlands in time.

219
00:19:03.925 --> 00:19:07.439
But right now.
Rook's Rest is an easy target

220
00:19:07.440 --> 00:19:09.441
and a worthy effort.

221
00:19:10.483 --> 00:19:13.486
Don't you agree.
my king?

222
00:19:26.458 --> 00:19:29.502
Come.

223
00:19:33.882 --> 00:19:35.508
Lord Larys.

224
00:19:39.346 --> 00:19:41.848
I thought I'd look in
on you. Your Grace.

225
00:19:41.849 --> 00:19:44.351
after your absence
from the small council.

226
00:19:44.352 --> 00:19:46.435
I feared something
was amiss.

227
00:19:46.436 --> 00:19:49.481
You're kind
to do so. my lord.

228
00:19:49.482 --> 00:19:52.107
but indulgence
was my sin.

229
00:19:52.108 --> 00:19:55.320
I... ventured into the lamprey pie
at last night's supper.

230
00:19:55.321 --> 00:19:57.322
Too far. I fear.

231
00:20:00.367 --> 00:20:01.993
Mm.

232
00:20:03.703 --> 00:20:06.164
That is a rich indulgence.

233
00:20:06.998 --> 00:20:10.438
But I believe
it is a sin to deny your appetites.

234
00:20:10.439 --> 00:20:13.880
They are what make us fully alive
as mortal men.

235
00:20:18.176 --> 00:20:20.637
Was anything of note
discussed at the council?

236
00:20:20.638 --> 00:20:22.554
Daemon having
seized Harrenhal

237
00:20:22.555 --> 00:20:25.474
and His Grace's
resulting displeasure.

238
00:20:25.475 --> 00:20:29.354
I would've thought you would be
the most aggrieved. my lord.

239
00:20:30.397 --> 00:20:32.607
I see it as a loss
for our greater good.

240
00:20:34.192 --> 00:20:36.568
Dragonstone's attentions
are greatly divided.

241
00:20:36.569 --> 00:20:40.740
First in the Riverlands and the Gullet.
and now the Crownlands.

242
00:20:40.741 --> 00:20:43.472
Ser Criston wins every challenge
he faces there.

243
00:20:43.473 --> 00:20:46.204
That truth alone
is like to incite Rhaenyra's fury.

244
00:20:46.913 --> 00:20:49.541
He's covered himself
in glory. to be sure.

245
00:20:50.709 --> 00:20:53.211
And you must
worry for him?

246
00:20:53.628 --> 00:20:55.880
Your sworn sword...

247
00:20:56.881 --> 00:20:58.590
on the march.

248
00:20:58.591 --> 00:21:00.238
ever exposed
to dragons?

249
00:21:00.239 --> 00:21:01.886
It is a perilous road.

250
00:21:05.223 --> 00:21:07.225
Ser Criston is
the Hand of the King.

251
00:21:08.560 --> 00:21:11.229
We should all pray for his victory
and safe return.

252
00:21:12.272 --> 00:21:13.481
Indeed.

253
00:21:23.450 --> 00:21:26.911
If I may be so bold.
my queen...

254
00:21:32.584 --> 00:21:35.003
you have not seemed
yourself of late.

255
00:21:36.588 --> 00:21:38.923
Only weeks ago.
my lord husband was alive

256
00:21:38.924 --> 00:21:40.967
and the realm
was at peace.

257
00:21:41.426 --> 00:21:45.096
Now. I've... barely had the hours
to grieve one tragedy

258
00:21:45.097 --> 00:21:46.263
before suffering
the next.

259
00:21:46.264 --> 00:21:49.934
I regret
if I have not been myself.

260
00:21:51.978 --> 00:21:52.979
Hm.

261
00:21:53.480 --> 00:21:56.107
I did not know you shared
your lord husband's love...

262
00:21:57.192 --> 00:21:59.027
for the histories.

263
00:22:00.445 --> 00:22:04.115
If not his love. then certainly an...
an abiding interest.

264
00:22:05.200 --> 00:22:06.951
The voices of history
guided Viserys.

265
00:22:06.952 --> 00:22:08.912
He knew that
his wisdom alone

266
00:22:08.913 --> 00:22:10.080
could only
reach so far.

267
00:22:10.455 --> 00:22:12.957
Do you think that is why
he changed his mind...

268
00:22:14.292 --> 00:22:16.919
in the end?

269
00:22:16.920 --> 00:22:20.840
No matter how suited he thought
Rhaenyra for the crown.

270
00:22:20.841 --> 00:22:25.469
the. uh. voices of history.
as you say.

271
00:22:25.470 --> 00:22:28.347
would have told him
how the realm would react

272
00:22:28.348 --> 00:22:30.809
- to her succession.
- It was impossible to know what steered his thoughts

273
00:22:30.810 --> 00:22:32.686
in those final hours.

274
00:22:33.978 --> 00:22:36.147
Do you now doubt
his intentions?

275
00:22:43.822 --> 00:22:46.491
Rhaenyra's supporters
will believe what they wish.

276
00:22:47.158 --> 00:22:49.160
And so will Aegon's.

277
00:22:49.994 --> 00:22:54.498
The war will be fought.
many will die...

278
00:22:54.499 --> 00:22:57.168
and the victor will eventually
ascend the throne.

279
00:22:59.045 --> 00:23:02.674
The significance
of Viserys's intentions died with him.

280
00:23:08.847 --> 00:23:10.849
Yes. it did.

281
00:24:47.737 --> 00:24:50.407
It's a touch late
to be stalkin' about a strange castle.

282
00:24:50.408 --> 00:24:52.492
putting its people
to the sword.

283
00:24:52.493 --> 00:24:53.785
You.

284
00:24:54.953 --> 00:24:56.788
I'm called Alys.

285
00:24:57.372 --> 00:24:58.832
Strong?

286
00:24:58.833 --> 00:25:00.041
Rivers.

287
00:25:01.126 --> 00:25:02.293
A bastard.

288
00:25:02.836 --> 00:25:05.463
Once you get to know me.
you'll find I'm not so bad.

289
00:25:06.214 --> 00:25:10.677
- So what are you then? Some kind of maester?
- In a manner of speaking.

290
00:25:10.678 --> 00:25:14.347
I inherited the duties
after the last one fled in the night.

291
00:25:14.348 --> 00:25:17.308
- Fled? Why?
- Just never settled in.

292
00:25:20.020 --> 00:25:22.063
How are you
settling in?

293
00:25:22.731 --> 00:25:25.942
I've come to know
the face of tortured rest well enough.

294
00:25:26.526 --> 00:25:29.799
Sleep can be...
thin in this place.

295
00:25:29.800 --> 00:25:33.074
What would you know
of my sleep?

296
00:25:34.159 --> 00:25:38.496
Harrenhal's been cursed
since its first stone was laid.

297
00:25:38.497 --> 00:25:40.957
Black Harren felled
the grove of weirwood trees

298
00:25:40.958 --> 00:25:43.167
that grew on these lands.

299
00:25:43.168 --> 00:25:45.378
Heart trees. imbued
with the spirits of those

300
00:25:45.379 --> 00:25:47.504
who lived long
before he came.

301
00:25:47.505 --> 00:25:51.217
- It's said their whispers can still be heard sometimes.
- A midwife's tale.

302
00:25:51.218 --> 00:25:54.888
Mm. the very bed you sleep in was made
from such a heart tree.

303
00:25:56.598 --> 00:26:00.185
Have you experienced
anything... of note?

304
00:26:00.852 --> 00:26:03.271
You are a strange
kind of woman.

305
00:26:03.688 --> 00:26:06.483
I'm no woman at all.
I'm a barn owl.

306
00:26:06.484 --> 00:26:08.443
Cursed to live
in human form.

307
00:26:09.944 --> 00:26:14.324
So. you've come here
after quarreling with your wife?

308
00:26:14.325 --> 00:26:15.408
What?

309
00:26:16.743 --> 00:26:19.371
You arrive here alone
to claim the castle

310
00:26:19.372 --> 00:26:21.623
and yet.
send no ravens.

311
00:26:23.875 --> 00:26:26.544
Do you now plan
to make your own claim?

312
00:26:27.045 --> 00:26:29.214
- Perhaps to prove yourself to her.
- Do not try me

313
00:26:29.215 --> 00:26:31.215
with your insolence. witch.

314
00:26:31.216 --> 00:26:33.092
It's a hard thing.
I imagine. to give

315
00:26:33.093 --> 00:26:36.262
obeisance to one
who replaced you as heir.

316
00:26:38.723 --> 00:26:41.392
And a woman too.
A...

317
00:26:41.393 --> 00:26:44.062
girl child you
bounced on your knee.

318
00:26:46.398 --> 00:26:49.192
I mean. does it please
you that her legitimacy is contested?

319
00:26:49.193 --> 00:26:51.276
As you stand here...

320
00:26:51.277 --> 00:26:53.904
with a castle
and a dragon...

321
00:26:53.905 --> 00:26:56.116
attempting to draw
an army of men.

322
00:27:01.246 --> 00:27:02.831
Here. Drink this.

323
00:27:04.749 --> 00:27:08.420
You'll need your sleep
if you're to win this place to your side.

324
00:27:17.929 --> 00:27:19.556
I now rule my house as regent

325
00:27:19.557 --> 00:27:21.391
until my nephew Benjicot
comes of age.

326
00:27:26.771 --> 00:27:29.773
The Brackens
are venal cravens.

327
00:27:29.774 --> 00:27:31.609
and they must pay
for their treachery

328
00:27:31.610 --> 00:27:33.445
against the laws
of gods and men.

329
00:27:34.612 --> 00:27:36.656
And against the crown.

330
00:27:36.657 --> 00:27:38.240
Who are you?

331
00:27:38.241 --> 00:27:39.909
Ser Willem Blackwood
of House Blackwood.

332
00:27:39.910 --> 00:27:42.954
Your Grace.
as I said.

333
00:27:46.791 --> 00:27:47.959
Well met.

334
00:27:49.002 --> 00:27:50.836
What might
I do for you?

335
00:27:50.837 --> 00:27:54.507
It was you who summoned me.
Your Grace.

336
00:27:54.508 --> 00:27:56.342
I was given
to understand

337
00:27:56.343 --> 00:27:58.177
that you
wanted an army.

338
00:27:58.178 --> 00:27:59.970
Well.
who doesn't these days?

339
00:27:59.971 --> 00:28:01.848
You Blackwoods certainly never
miss a chance

340
00:28:01.849 --> 00:28:05.310
to bloody your swords...
do you?

341
00:28:05.977 --> 00:28:07.144
Some 20 years ago.

342
00:28:07.145 --> 00:28:09.313
my lord bent the knee
to King Viserys

343
00:28:09.314 --> 00:28:12.692
and acknowledged the Princess Rhaenyra
as his rightful heir.

344
00:28:12.693 --> 00:28:14.485
So you fight
for this old oath?

345
00:28:14.486 --> 00:28:17.489
Not. of course. for your thousand-year-old
feud with the Brackens.

346
00:28:19.199 --> 00:28:22.327
I once vied
for Queen Rhaenyra's hand...

347
00:28:22.328 --> 00:28:24.662
before she wed
Ser Laenor.

348
00:28:24.663 --> 00:28:26.998
I always liked
her spirit.

349
00:28:27.540 --> 00:28:29.500
She had the true blood
of the dragon.

350
00:28:29.501 --> 00:28:33.505
And you're prepared to march without
the leave of your lord...

351
00:28:55.735 --> 00:28:57.612
Your Grace?

352
00:28:58.947 --> 00:29:00.698
And once you
and your dragon

353
00:29:00.699 --> 00:29:03.868
bring the queen's justice
to the Brackens...

354
00:29:04.285 --> 00:29:06.287
our armies will be yours.

355
00:29:15.547 --> 00:29:17.819
Our lords in the Crownlands
are grousing.

356
00:29:17.820 --> 00:29:20.093
Their herds of livestock
struggle to keep pace

357
00:29:20.094 --> 00:29:21.885
with the dragons'
relentless appetites.

358
00:29:21.886 --> 00:29:24.701
- Vhagar's in particular.
- They can either provide

359
00:29:24.702 --> 00:29:27.517
the crown what it needs.
or we can claim their holdings.

360
00:29:27.518 --> 00:29:29.540
Oh. that would be a relief.

361
00:29:29.541 --> 00:29:31.615
as we have no more coin
to lend to the effort.

362
00:29:31.616 --> 00:29:33.690
Resources are certainly
growing no more plentiful

363
00:29:33.691 --> 00:29:35.357
in the face
of the blockade.

364
00:29:35.358 --> 00:29:37.277
The demand on the blacksmiths.
armorers and tanners

365
00:29:37.278 --> 00:29:38.528
for equipment has
only grown apace

366
00:29:38.529 --> 00:29:40.070
with Ser Criston's army.

367
00:29:40.071 --> 00:29:42.073
Well. Cole's done splendidly.
at the least.

368
00:29:42.074 --> 00:29:44.074
turning every castle
and army he's faced.

369
00:29:44.075 --> 00:29:47.120
including Duskendale. gods bless him.

370
00:29:47.121 --> 00:29:49.204
The Kingmaker.
they're calling him.

371
00:29:49.205 --> 00:29:51.415
And with Aemond
and Vhagar also at the ready.

372
00:29:51.416 --> 00:29:53.626
we are a formidable opponent.

373
00:29:54.919 --> 00:29:56.629
You bore me.

374
00:29:59.466 --> 00:30:01.468
You all bore me.

375
00:30:16.107 --> 00:30:20.111
Perhaps Ser Criston will be able to procure

376
00:30:20.112 --> 00:30:22.112
more livestock
through his campaign.

377
00:30:22.113 --> 00:30:24.866
Any coin we can save will be
a welcome bounty.

378
00:30:34.793 --> 00:30:36.251
What are you
doing here?

379
00:30:36.252 --> 00:30:37.836
Where are your
father's books?

380
00:30:37.837 --> 00:30:39.798
I ordered them removed.

381
00:30:39.799 --> 00:30:41.237
With no thought
to the centuries

382
00:30:41.238 --> 00:30:42.676
of knowledge
in those pages.

383
00:30:49.349 --> 00:30:50.975
Your Grace.

384
00:30:52.519 --> 00:30:55.188
I removed them.
I didn't burn them.

385
00:31:00.402 --> 00:31:01.819
What is it?

386
00:31:01.820 --> 00:31:04.155
They don't care what I think.

387
00:31:06.825 --> 00:31:09.159
- Who. Aegon?
- My council.

388
00:31:09.160 --> 00:31:11.328
Cole. Aemond.
They pursue their campaign

389
00:31:11.329 --> 00:31:13.498
without seeking my aid.
or even my thoughts.

390
00:31:16.710 --> 00:31:18.169
What thoughts
would you have?

391
00:31:19.671 --> 00:31:21.506
Wh... I'm the king.

392
00:31:25.010 --> 00:31:28.388
Do you think simply wearing
the crown imbues you with wisdom?

393
00:31:34.519 --> 00:31:37.939
Those men at your
council table...

394
00:31:38.898 --> 00:31:40.942
earned their seats.

395
00:31:41.401 --> 00:31:44.299
It was my hope that
once enthroned.

396
00:31:44.300 --> 00:31:47.198
you would honor
the burden of your new duties.

397
00:31:47.199 --> 00:31:49.074
be silent.

398
00:31:49.075 --> 00:31:52.746
and strive to learn from the more studied
minds around you.

399
00:31:54.247 --> 00:31:57.250
In the hope that you might be
half the king your father was.

400
00:31:58.877 --> 00:32:01.296
- Tread carefully.
- Or what?

401
00:32:03.048 --> 00:32:06.050
You'll hang me.
as you did your ratcatchers?

402
00:32:06.051 --> 00:32:09.054
Or have me banished.
as you did your Hand?

403
00:32:10.180 --> 00:32:11.597
I ruled

404
00:32:11.598 --> 00:32:14.016
in your father's absence
throughout his long illness.

405
00:32:14.017 --> 00:32:16.728
and Otto Hightower was
as cunning a statesman as ever lived.

406
00:32:16.729 --> 00:32:21.941
You should humbly be
seeking our opinions and counsel.

407
00:32:24.277 --> 00:32:26.279
You have no idea
the sacrifices that were made

408
00:32:26.280 --> 00:32:28.573
to put you on that throne.

409
00:32:33.244 --> 00:32:34.245
Wha...

410
00:32:36.456 --> 00:32:39.125
What would you
have me do. Mother?

411
00:32:40.418 --> 00:32:42.837
Do simply what
is needed of you:

412
00:32:44.589 --> 00:32:45.965
nothing.

413
00:33:16.121 --> 00:33:18.164
On your feet!

414
00:33:19.457 --> 00:33:21.459
To Rook's Rest!

415
00:33:22.627 --> 00:33:24.045
To battle!

416
00:33:29.175 --> 00:33:31.135
It's broad daylight.

417
00:33:31.136 --> 00:33:34.639
We must hold here and ready ourselves
to lay siege at nightfall.

418
00:33:34.640 --> 00:33:36.641
We shall move now
and strike by day.

419
00:33:36.642 --> 00:33:37.996
They will not expect it.

420
00:33:37.997 --> 00:33:39.351
They will not expect it

421
00:33:39.352 --> 00:33:41.521
because it is
fucking madness.

422
00:33:43.314 --> 00:33:44.649
Did you forget
the little encounter

423
00:33:44.650 --> 00:33:46.359
we had on the road
to Rosby?

424
00:33:47.027 --> 00:33:48.236
I did not.

425
00:33:50.155 --> 00:33:53.158
Dragonstone and their dragons
are just across the bay.

426
00:33:54.576 --> 00:33:56.578
What? Grown tired
of living. have you?

427
00:33:57.537 --> 00:33:59.164
Are you afraid. Ser?

428
00:34:00.165 --> 00:34:02.500
Worse. I'm rational.

429
00:34:04.544 --> 00:34:06.503
We advance.

430
00:34:26.566 --> 00:34:28.359
I see no other choice.

431
00:34:28.360 --> 00:34:30.862
- We need to send a dragon.
- Where?

432
00:34:34.783 --> 00:34:37.034
To support the war

433
00:34:37.035 --> 00:34:40.205
that your vassals have been fighting
in your absence...

434
00:34:40.206 --> 00:34:41.456
Your Grace.

435
00:34:42.749 --> 00:34:46.001
Cole's host has grown
since riding abroad.

436
00:34:46.002 --> 00:34:48.546
He raised the levies of both
Rosby and Stokeworth

437
00:34:48.547 --> 00:34:51.091
and. with their combined strength.
sacked Duskendale.

438
00:34:51.092 --> 00:34:52.716
Duskendale?

439
00:34:52.717 --> 00:34:54.760
The city has fallen.

440
00:34:54.761 --> 00:34:56.721
Many Darklyn men
declared for Aegon.

441
00:34:56.722 --> 00:34:58.682
Those who refused
were put to the sword.

442
00:34:58.683 --> 00:35:00.538
What of my father?

443
00:35:00.539 --> 00:35:02.393
He kept his oath.

444
00:35:02.394 --> 00:35:04.270
Cole took
his head for it.

445
00:35:06.481 --> 00:35:09.191
Where have you been.
these last days?

446
00:35:09.192 --> 00:35:11.903
You vanished without
so much as a word.

447
00:35:12.612 --> 00:35:15.740
Well. I apologize for my absence
and the secrecy.

448
00:35:15.741 --> 00:35:17.742
but such
was necessary.

449
00:35:18.576 --> 00:35:20.578
I went
to King's Landing.

450
00:35:21.579 --> 00:35:23.247
To what possible end?

451
00:35:23.248 --> 00:35:25.812
To meet Queen Alicent
and sue for peace.

452
00:35:25.813 --> 00:35:28.378
- You saw Alicent?
- Yes. I did.

453
00:35:28.379 --> 00:35:30.754
You could've been taken
or slain!

454
00:35:30.755 --> 00:35:34.634
I inherited 80 years of peace
from my father.

455
00:35:34.635 --> 00:35:36.301
Before I was
to end it.

456
00:35:36.302 --> 00:35:39.347
I needed to know
that there was no other path.

457
00:35:41.933 --> 00:35:43.518
And now I do.

458
00:35:47.105 --> 00:35:50.232
Only one choice
remains to me:

459
00:35:50.233 --> 00:35:53.361
either I win my claim
or die.

460
00:35:54.988 --> 00:35:57.282
We stand
at the ready.

461
00:35:58.158 --> 00:36:00.452
Cole's victories have
only emboldened him.

462
00:36:00.453 --> 00:36:02.308
He marches
on Rook's Rest.

463
00:36:02.309 --> 00:36:04.163
His host was
just hours away

464
00:36:04.164 --> 00:36:07.292
- when Lord Staunton's ravens took wing.
- Why Rook's Rest?

465
00:36:07.293 --> 00:36:08.667
After Duskendale?

466
00:36:08.668 --> 00:36:10.836
It is but a small
coastal keep.

467
00:36:10.837 --> 00:36:14.631
'Cause Lord Staunton is
a member of this council.

468
00:36:14.632 --> 00:36:18.595
And because his castle is small
and vulnerable and there for the taking.

469
00:36:18.596 --> 00:36:21.013
Cole knows we have no army
on the mainland.

470
00:36:21.014 --> 00:36:23.600
- He is brazen.
- He is daring us to act.

471
00:36:23.601 --> 00:36:26.728
We need to send
a dragon.

472
00:36:33.568 --> 00:36:37.572
There are those who have mistaken
my caution for weakness.

473
00:36:42.202 --> 00:36:44.204
Let that be
their undoing.

474
00:36:45.080 --> 00:36:47.331
- I will go.
- My queen...

475
00:36:47.332 --> 00:36:50.168
- You cannot.
- I will not lose dragons to war

476
00:36:50.169 --> 00:36:51.543
whilst I hide here
in my castle.

477
00:36:51.544 --> 00:36:54.714
Our allies raise their banners
for you. Mother.

478
00:36:54.715 --> 00:36:57.300
Yes. they do.

479
00:36:57.301 --> 00:36:59.886
If you die.
all is lost.

480
00:36:59.887 --> 00:37:01.512
- Send me.
- No.

481
00:37:01.513 --> 00:37:03.452
I will burn Cole's lines
and withdraw before King's Landing

482
00:37:03.453 --> 00:37:05.653
- could even raise the alarm.
- You lack the experience.

483
00:37:08.395 --> 00:37:10.689
You must send me.
Your Grace.

484
00:37:12.941 --> 00:37:14.671
Meleys is your
largest dragon

485
00:37:14.672 --> 00:37:16.403
and no stranger
to battle.

486
00:37:19.197 --> 00:37:21.032
I will meet Cole.

487
00:38:29.642 --> 00:38:31.478
I wish only to fight for you.

488
00:38:31.479 --> 00:38:33.563
for your claim
and mine.

489
00:38:33.564 --> 00:38:35.023
I...

490
00:38:36.441 --> 00:38:38.121
There's something
I need to tell you. Jace.

491
00:38:40.653 --> 00:38:44.114
Something...
I should've told you

492
00:38:44.115 --> 00:38:46.326
when you first became
heir to the throne.

493
00:38:47.452 --> 00:38:50.559
<i>It's a secret
that Viserys told me</i>

494
00:38:50.560 --> 00:38:53.666
<i>when he named
me his successor.</i>

495
00:38:53.667 --> 00:38:57.024
<i>And it has passed
from king to heir...</i>

496
00:38:57.025 --> 00:39:00.382
<i>since Aegon
the Conqueror's time.</i>

497
00:39:08.682 --> 00:39:11.017
<i>I never told you
because I was unsure</i>

498
00:39:11.018 --> 00:39:14.019
<i>that I believed it myself.</i>

499
00:39:14.020 --> 00:39:17.189
<i>The Targaryen who sits
the Iron Throne</i>

500
00:39:17.190 --> 00:39:19.671
<i>is not just
a king or a queen.</i>

501
00:39:19.672 --> 00:39:22.153
<i>They are a Protector.</i>

502
00:39:26.574 --> 00:39:28.827
<i>Ordained to lead
the Seven Kingdoms.</i>

503
00:39:28.828 --> 00:39:30.745
<i>to strengthen them...</i>

504
00:39:32.664 --> 00:39:36.668
<i>...and to unite them
against a common foe.</i>

505
00:39:41.214 --> 00:39:45.467
<i>Viserys chose me
to succeed him.</i>

506
00:39:45.468 --> 00:39:48.179
<i>He held to this
the whole of his life.</i>

507
00:39:53.727 --> 00:39:57.354
<i>My father believed
that I. alone.</i>

508
00:39:57.355 --> 00:40:00.065
<i>was meant to be
this Protector.</i>

509
00:40:00.066 --> 00:40:03.153
They're 1.400-.
1.500-strong at least. my lord.

510
00:40:04.654 --> 00:40:06.155
<i>But to unite the realm.</i>

511
00:40:06.156 --> 00:40:08.742
<i>I had to send
the dragons to war.</i>

512
00:40:16.875 --> 00:40:20.545
The horrors I have just loosed
cannot be for a crown alone.

513
00:40:22.630 --> 00:40:24.715
<i>That is why I must believe</i>

514
00:40:24.716 --> 00:40:27.886
<i>what Viserys told me
when he named me his heir.</i>

515
00:40:27.887 --> 00:40:30.888
<i>What Jaehaerys had told him.</i>

516
00:40:30.889 --> 00:40:33.350
<i>And what I will now
tell you.</i>

517
00:40:36.061 --> 00:40:37.103
What is it?

518
00:40:43.443 --> 00:40:45.653
Aegon the Conqueror's Dream.

519
00:40:47.822 --> 00:40:51.493
He called it
"The Song of Ice and Fire."

520
00:41:01.252 --> 00:41:03.254
Loose! New rank!

521
00:41:04.422 --> 00:41:07.467
Loose! New rank!

522
00:41:08.593 --> 00:41:10.929
Loose! New rank!

523
00:41:15.600 --> 00:41:16.643
Push it!

524
00:41:17.811 --> 00:41:19.646
Dragon!

525
00:41:19.647 --> 00:41:21.272
Dragon!

526
00:41:25.777 --> 00:41:28.446
To the Seven Hells
with you. Cole!

527
00:41:28.863 --> 00:41:31.073
You may as well have sounded horns
to announce our coming!

528
00:41:31.074 --> 00:41:33.284
Order the Darklyn levies
to break off and move ahead.

529
00:41:33.285 --> 00:41:35.161
We must keep the dragon's
attention divided.

530
00:41:35.162 --> 00:41:37.392
- Make the signal.
- What signal?

531
00:41:37.393 --> 00:41:39.624
All is going to plan.

532
00:43:11.216 --> 00:43:12.883
Forward. Sunfyre!

533
00:43:12.884 --> 00:43:15.095
Faster!

534
00:43:15.637 --> 00:43:17.722
Dragon!

535
00:43:17.723 --> 00:43:19.578
Whose dragon
is that?

536
00:43:19.579 --> 00:43:21.434
His Grace.
the king's.

537
00:43:22.560 --> 00:43:24.541
This was your
secret plot. Cole?

538
00:43:24.542 --> 00:43:26.522
For the king himself
to lay ambush

539
00:43:26.523 --> 00:43:28.858
- and mayhaps die in the attempt?!
- No!

540
00:43:28.859 --> 00:43:30.735
Loose more
signal arrows!

541
00:43:34.114 --> 00:43:36.408
Stalwart men
of House Targaryen.

542
00:43:37.659 --> 00:43:41.036
your king
has joined you!

543
00:43:41.037 --> 00:43:43.810
Hold to your courage!
Hold to your wits!

544
00:43:43.811 --> 00:43:46.584
For the Seven have
blessed and shielded

545
00:43:46.585 --> 00:43:49.316
this host
with divine purpose!

546
00:43:49.317 --> 00:43:51.975
For the one true king.
Aegon!

547
00:43:51.976 --> 00:43:54.634
Advance!

548
00:44:02.767 --> 00:44:04.853
Where are you.
Aemond?

549
00:44:19.951 --> 00:44:21.453
<i>Dracarys!</i>

550
00:45:00.408 --> 00:45:02.451
Another one there!

551
00:45:02.452 --> 00:45:04.704
Send a volley
to those Rosby men!

552
00:45:04.705 --> 00:45:06.748
Give them no quarter!

553
00:45:16.174 --> 00:45:18.176
We'd best get you
to cover. my lord.

554
00:46:06.850 --> 00:46:08.768
Thank the gods!

555
00:46:10.270 --> 00:46:11.521
<i>Dracarys!</i>

556
00:46:11.522 --> 00:46:12.564
Ah!

557
00:46:17.068 --> 00:46:19.154
No!

558
00:46:38.277 --> 00:46:40.133
Your Grace!

559
00:51:46.564 --> 00:51:48.733
Fall in behind me!

560
00:51:49.734 --> 00:51:51.735
Into the breach!

561
00:52:23.268 --> 00:52:25.770
The king has fallen.
We must find him.

562
00:53:15.862 --> 00:53:17.155
Aemond!

563
00:53:32.629 --> 00:53:34.673
Where's His Grace?
